title: Catechin-5-O-glucoside
data: Catechin 5-O-glucoside is a flavanol glucoside. It can be found in rhubarb and in the bark of Rhaphiolepis umbellata.[2] It can also be formed from (+)-catechin by plant-cultured cells of Eucalyptus perriniana.[3] This article about an aromatic compound is a stub.
